{"parse":{"title":"Solarball","pageid":31343719,"revid":828068627,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The <b>solarball</b> is a water purification device based on <a href=\"/wiki/Portable_water_purification#Solar_distillation\" title=\"Portable water purification\">evaporation purification</a>. It consists of a clear plastic sphere which users would fill with water and then wear on their heads.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> A solarball can produce three liters of clean water per day. \n</p><p>Sunlight enters inside of the ball passing through transparent layer and evaporates dirty water, in the other side of the ball, water vapours condense and form <a href=\"/wiki/Clean_water\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Clean water\">clean water</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> It was invented by Jonathan Liow (\u7d04\u7ff0\u00b7\u5ed6\u4e2d\u840a), an Australian student who is studying Industrial Design.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Solarball&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.gizmag.com/solarball-creates-drinkable-water/18270/\">Student-designed Solarball creates drinkable water</a>, By Ben Coxworth, March 30, 2011.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"http://edition.cnn.com/video/#/video/tech/2011/03/31/nr.solarball.clean.water.cnn\">http://edition.cnn.com/video/#/video/tech/2011/03/31/nr.solarball.clean.water.cnn</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"http://www.ubergizmo.com/2011/03/solarball-purify-water/\">http://www.ubergizmo.com/2011/03/solarball-purify-water/</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Solarball&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20120818142610/http://greenliving.nationalgeographic.com/use-solar-power-purify-water-3062.html\">How Do I Use Solar Power to Purify Water?</a></li></ul>\n<p><br />\n</p>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"background:transparent\"><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"/wiki/File:Icon_river_tributary_R.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Stub icon\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c8/Icon_river_tributary_R.svg/30px-Icon_river_tributary_R.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"33\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c8/Icon_river_tributary_R.svg/45px-Icon_river_tributary_R.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c8/Icon_river_tributary_R.svg/60px-Icon_river_tributary_R.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"180\" data-file-height=\"200\" /></a></td><td><i>This <a href=\"/wiki/Water_supply\" title=\"Water supply\">water supply</a>\u2013related article is a <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Stub\" title=\"Wikipedia:Stub\">stub</a>. You can